# Matex Canadian Compliance Rules

## Provincial Tax Application
Tax must be calculated based on the **seller province** (supply) and **buyer province** (destination).
Stored in `tax_mcp.invoices` with separate columns for each tax type.

| Province | Tax Type | Rate |
|---|---|---|
| ON, NB, NS, NL, PE | HST | 13–15% |
| BC | GST + PST | 5% + 7% |
| AB, SK*, MB* | GST only | 5% |
| QC | GST + QST | 5% + 9.975% |

Rules:
- Always store `seller_province` and `buyer_province` on the invoice.
- Recycled metals and qualifying scrap may be zero-rated for GST/HST — verify the material category before applying tax.
- Input Tax Credits (ITCs) are tracked per period in `tax_mcp.tax_remittances`.
- Never use a flat tax rate; always look up the correct province pair.

## Invoice Number Format
All invoices follow the format: `MTX-YYYY-NNNNNN` (e.g., `MTX-2026-000042`).
- `YYYY` is the calendar year of issuance.
- `NNNNNN` is a zero-padded sequential number reset each year.
- The `invoice_number` column has a `UNIQUE` constraint — enforce this before insert.

```typescript
// Generate invoice number
function generateInvoiceNumber(year: number, seq: number): string {
  return `MTX-${year}-${String(seq).padStart(6, '0')}`;
}
```

## CRA Business Number Validation
Canadian Business Numbers (BN) follow the format: `XXXXXXXXX RT YYYY`
- 9-digit root number + program identifier (`RT` for GST/HST) + 4-digit account number.
- Stored in `profile_mcp.companies.business_number` and `gst_hst_number`.

```typescript
// Validate CRA BN format
const CRA_BN_REGEX = /^\d{9}(RT\d{4})?$/;
function validateCraBN(bn: string): boolean {
  return CRA_BN_REGEX.test(bn.replace(/\s/g, ''));
}
```

## Weight Certification — CAW Scale Tickets
For all weight disputes and final settlement:
- The scale certificate number (`scale_certificate`) must reference a valid Weights and Measures Canada (CAW) certified scale.
- `scale_certified = true` requires a certificate number — never set without one.
- The 4-point weight chain authority order: `w4_third_party` > `w3_buyer` > `w2_carrier` > `w1_seller`.
- If `w4_third_party` exists, it is the authoritative weight for price adjustment calculation.

## PIPEDA-Compliant Data Handling
Under PIPEDA (Personal Information Protection and Electronic Documents Act):
- Collect only the minimum personal data required for KYC level being verified.
- KYC document files (`kyc_mcp.documents.file_url`) must be stored encrypted at rest.
- Users can request deletion of personal data — implement a soft-delete pattern that anonymizes PII while retaining financial records for the CRA-required 7-year retention period.
- Never log full PII (SIN, passport number, DOB) in `log_mcp.audit_log` — use `input_hash` instead.
- Data residency: all Supabase storage and database must be hosted in Canadian data centres (ca-central-1).

## Environmental Permit Tracking
Listings for regulated materials (certain metals, e-waste, hazardous) require environmental permits:
```json
// listing_mcp.listings.environmental_permits
[{ "permit_type": "provincial_transport", "number": "ON-2026-12345", "expiry": "2027-01-01" }]
```
- Listings without a required permit must stay in `pending_review` status.
- Expired permits must trigger an automated listing suspension.

## Hazardous Materials (Hazmat)
Shipments carrying hazmat materials must have `hazmat_class` set (not `none`).
Hazmat classes map to Transport Canada dangerous goods classifications (TDG regulations):
- Class 8 (corrosives) — common for lead-acid batteries.
- Class 9 (miscellaneous) — common for lithium-ion battery scrap.
Carriers transporting hazmat must have appropriate TDG certification recorded in their profile.

## Currency
- All amounts on the platform are in **CAD** by default.
- `pricing_mcp.market_prices` may store USD (LME, Fastmarkets) — always note `currency` column.
- When displaying or converting LME prices to CAD, use the Bank of Canada daily rate — never use a hardcoded conversion factor.

## Data Retention Schedule
| Data Category | Retention |
|---|---|
| Financial records (invoices, transactions) | 7 years (CRA requirement) |
| KYC documents | 5 years post-account closure |
| Audit logs | 7 years |
| Messages/communications | 3 years |
| Session tokens | 90 days after expiry |
